commitResults.messageBody: * Update Duke.java to include Greet, Echo and Exit features
* Update Duke.java to include Add and List features

* Add Task.java to support representation of tasks
* Update Duke.java to include Done feature

* Update Task.java to make it an abstract class that represents a task
* Add TaskType.java enumeration to define different types of tasks
* Add TaskWithDateTime.java to make it an abstract class that represents
a task with date/time
* Add ToDo.java, Deadline.java and Event.java to support representation
of three types of tasks
* Update Duke.java to support tracking of three types of tasks

* Update input.txt to include inputs for automated text UI testing
* Update EXPECTED.txt to include expected outputs for automated text
UI testing

* Add DukeException.java to handle any exceptions during program
execution
* Add Ui.java to handle input and output interactions
* Update Duke.java to handle errors via exception handling
* Update Duke.java and Ui.java to include Delete feature

* Add Storage.java to handle file operations
* Update Task.java and TaskWithDateTime.java to include string
representation for save format
* Update Duke.java to save tasks in the hard disk automatically
whenever the task list changes

* Update TaskWithDateTime.java with the logic to process date and
time input with yyyy-mm-dd hhmm format into LocalDate and LocalTime
format for output
* Update Deadline.java and Event.java to replace date and time
information taken directly from the input with the processed date
and time information for output
* Update Duke.java to support the software in understanding date
and time in yyyy-mm-dd hhmm format by making minor changes to the
existing implementation when processing date and time of Deadline
and Event tasks

* Update Duke.java, TaskWithDateTime.java, Deadline.java and
Event.java with minor changes to the existing implementation
when processing date and time of Deadline and Event tasks

Make the code more OOP by extracting out more classes

* Add Command.java (interface), AddCommand.java, AddToDoCommand.java,
AddDeadlineCommand.java, AddEventCommand.java, DeleteCommand.java,
ExitCommand.java, ListCommand.java, MarkCommand.java and
UnmarkCommand.java to handle Command execution
* Add CommandType.java enumeration to define different types of
commands
* Add Parser.java to handle the logic of parsing the user command
* Add TaskList.java to contain the list of tasks and handle operations
of adding, deleting and retrieving tasks
* Update Duke.java, Storage.java and Ui.java with changes to support
the implementation of more OOP
* Update TaskType.java Javadoc comments

* Add JUnit tests in AddCommandTest.java for AddCommand classes
(AddCommand.java, AddToDoCommand.java, AddDeadlineCommand.java
and AddEventCommand.java)
* Add JUnit tests in ParserTest.java for Parser.java
* Add JUnit tests in TaskTest.java for Task classes (Task.java,
TaskWithDateTime.java, ToDo.java, Deadline.java, Event.java)
* Update Storage.java to include getter methods for directory and
dataFile variables so that the variables can be accessed for JUnit
tests in AddCommandTest.java

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Level-8, fix minor bugs and enhance codes
commitResults.messageBody:
Update Level-8

* Add PrintCommand.java to print deadlines/events occurring on a
specific date
* Update other java files with changes to support the implementation
of filtering tasks which is activated when Print command is used
* Update the existing implementation to allow the execution of Mark,
Unmark and Delete commands on filtered tasks

Fix minor bugs

* Update UnmarkCommand.java to use taskNotDoneMessage instead of
taskDoneMessage
* Update Ui.java to remove additional spacing in taskInListMessage
method
* Update Task.java to make corrections to the wrong Javadoc comments
in setNotDone method

Enhance codes

* Update TaskWithDateTime.java to replace if-else code with ternary
operator for processing time input
* Update Javadoc comments for some java files

* Add FindCommand.java to find tasks by searching for a keyword in
the description
* Update other java files with changes to support the implementation
of filtering tasks which is activated when Find command is used

* Add ErrorMessage.java enumeration to consolidate and define error
messages as constants for reusability and to adhere to coding standard
* Review all java files and tweak some codes to adhere to coding
standard
* Add Javadoc comments for Parser.java

* Review Javadoc comments of all java files except Parser.java since
major changes have been made to Parser.java in branch-A-CodingStandard

* Add Gradle support to automate project builds
* Add Checkstyle configuration files to detect coding style violations
* Update java files to adhere to coding standard and pass Checkstyle by
correcting detected coding style violations

* Add GUI to Duke using JavaFX technology
* Update other java files and tweak some codes to support the
implementation of GUI
